FBIS4-27621 "dreas106_c_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 24 May 1994 North Korea U.S. Stages `Mobile Deployment Exercise' 22-23 May U.S. Stages `Mobile Deployment Exercise' 22-23 May SK2805022794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1100 GMT 24 May 94 SK2805022794 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1100 GMT 24 May 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to military sources, the U.S. imperialists conducted a series of aerial mobile deployment exercise on 22 and 23 May, lifting troops from U.S. bases in the Pacific area to South Korea. Pursuit-assault planes and VTOL [vertical takeoff and landing] assault planes that took off from overseas bases flew into the U.S. occupation Air Force bases in South Korea on 23 May. Prior to this, on 22 May, squadrons of assault planes and pursuit-assault planes that left a base in Japan flew into the U.S. bases in South Korea. This war exercise was aimed at examining overseas-based fighter planes' actual combat ability of rapid mobile deployment to South Korea. In the meantime, C-141 and C-130 transport planes carrying many troops of the aggression army and war equipment took off from U.S. Pacific bases and flew into the U.S. occupation Air Force bases in South Korea on 22 May, and the troops and murderous equipment carried by air were deployed in areas of operations. The U.S. imperialists' planned war exercise commotion is a grave challenge to peace and detente of Korea.
